    "id": "bernoulli_ineq",
    "title": "Bernoulli/binary KL scalar inequality",
    "display_label": "Bernoulli: $p\\log\\tfrac{p}{q}+(1-p)\\log\\tfrac{1-p}{1-q}\\ge 2(p-q)^2$",
    "informal_statement": "For all \(p,q\\in(0,1)\), \[p\\log\\!\\left(\\frac{p}{q}\\right)+(1-p)\\log\\!\\left(\\frac{1-p}{1-q}\\right)\\ge 2(p-q)^2.\]",
    "informal_proof_text": "Define \(F_q(p):=p\\log(p/q)+(1-p)\\log((1-p)/(1-q))-2(p-q)^2\) for \(p\\in(0,1)\) with \(q\\in(0,1)\) fixed. We show \(F_q(p)\\ge 0\) everywhere. By direct substitution \(F_q(q)=0\), and by direct computation \(F_q'(q)=0\). By the convexity lemma for \(F_q\) (which shows \(F_q''(p)\\ge 0\) on \((0,1)\)), \(F_q\) is convex and \(p=q\) is a critical point, hence a global minimizer. Therefore \(F_q(p)\\ge F_q(q)=0\) for all \(p\\in(0,1)\)."
