  {
    "id": "fq_convex",
    "title": "Convexity of $F_q$ via second-derivative bound",
    "display_label": "$F_q''(p)=\\tfrac{1}{p(1-p)}-4\\ge 0$",
    "informal_statement": "For fixed \(q\\in(0,1)\) and \(p\\in(0,1)\), let \(F_q(p):=p\\log(p/q)+(1-p)\\log((1-p)/(1-q))-2(p-q)^2\). Then \[F_q''(p)=\\frac{1}{p(1-p)}-4\\ge 0,\] so \(F_q\) is convex on \((0,1)\).",
    "informal_proof_text": "Differentiating term by term with respect to \(p\): \(\\frac{d}{dp}[p\\log(p/q)]=\\log(p/q)+1\) and \(\\frac{d}{dp}[(1-p)\\log((1-p)/(1-q))]=-\\log((1-p)/(1-q))-1\), so \(F_q'(p)=\\log\\!\\left(\\tfrac{p(1-q)}{q(1-p)}\\right)-4(p-q)\). Differentiating again: \(F_q''(p)=\\tfrac{1}{p}+\\tfrac{1}{1-p}-4=\\tfrac{1}{p(1-p)}-4\). Since \(p(1-p)\\le\\tfrac{1}{4}\) for all \(p\\in(0,1)\) (AM-GM), we have \(\\tfrac{1}{p(1-p)}\\ge 4\), and therefore \(F_q''(p)\\ge 0\) throughout \((0,1)\)."
  }
